Retail trader jo hota hai woh ek chhote capital ke saath market mein aata hai aur uski buy aur sell power chhoti hoti hai. New traders zyada tar tips par heavily depend karte hain.
DII (Domestic Institutional Investors) jaise Life Insurance Corporation of India jaisi insurance companies hoti hain, aur inki investment limit retail traders se kaafi zyada hoti hai.
FII (Foreign Institutional Investors) bade foreign institutions hote hain, jinke paas capital bahut zyada hota hai, aur inki buying aur selling power retail aur DII dono se kaafi badi hoti hai.(in dollars), NOT LOYAL 

RBI ka rate cut time to time check karna padta hai, kyunki Reserve Bank of India ke interest rate changes se market par direct impact padta hai—stocks, banking sector aur overall liquidity sab affect hote hain.

Morning mein global market ko check karna hota hai jisse market direction achhe se samajh aaye—jaise US markets (Dow Jones Industrial Average, NASDAQ Composite), Asia markets (Nikkei 225) aur India ka NIFTY 50 bhi direction lene mein help karta hai.(GLOBAL DIRECTION)

SGX Nifty (SGX Nifty) ek indicator hota hai jo batata hai ki Indian market open hone se pehle NIFTY 50 kis direction mein ja sakta hai.
SGX Nifty / global market check karne ka best time:

Early morning: 7:00 AM – 9:00 AM (India time)
